dely published poet, Sherman helps the reader understand the deep connection between disease and creativity—the ways in which we write out of our suffering. Wait Time will be of special interest to anyone facing a serious illness as well as to health-care providers, social workers, and psychologists working in the field. Its thoughtful observations on health, life priorities, time, and mortality will make it of interest to all readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKidneysxCancerxPatientszCanadavBiography. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aLife Writing. 4aMedical. 4aMedical: Public Health. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Medical.2bisacsh  aCanadian health care system.  acancer imagery.  acancer narrative.  acancer.  acoping with cancer.  acreativity and cancer.  adoctor/patient relationship.  aillness memoir.  akidney cancer.  ameaning of illness.  apoetry and cancer.  athinking through cancer.  await times for surgery.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630440uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112189740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771121897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771121897/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles